description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen within our Children Day Services Team for a Band 5 Nurse.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to welcome an enthusiastic Nurse to join the team. The successful candidate will be working with a dynamic team of Nurses and staff within the unit at Lister Hospital and the New Queen Elizabeth ll Hospital (QEII), caring for children from 0-16 years old.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The team provide care for a wide range of services including the Childrens Day Unit, Children&#39;s out patients ,Children&#39;s day surgery and Children&#39;s MRI. You&#39;ll work as a member of the nursing and wider multi-disciplinary teams, creating a welcoming, caring and safe environment for babies, children and families&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of your professional development you will be mentored and you will have the opportunity to attend relevant training and development courses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that RSCN or RN Child qualification is a must for this post. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;NB Internal Applicants - please be aware that you can apply but Internal Transfer Scheme will apply&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah Collins - Ward Manager for Children&#39;s Day Unit on 01438 286315&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lisa Walker Matron for acute Children&#39;s Services on 01438 285479&lt;/p&gt;
